The paper deals with computational complexity of a problem related to geometric graphs and discrete optimization. Specifically, it considers the problem of finding a minimum cardinality subset of unit disks that can isolate a given set of points in the plane. This problem involves concepts from computational geometry (unit disks, paths, intersections) and discrete optimization (minimum cardinality subset). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), as the problem involves graph theory and optimization.
